ce:section.ce:para:
According to IUPAC standards [23], ZnO/O-CQD displays type III adsorption-desorption isotherms of nitrogen (Fig. 3
                        ). Capillary condensation takes over as the pressure increases. A H3 hysteresis loop was observed in the case of the nanocomposite, suggesting that the wedge-shaped pores formed by the loose stacking of flaky particles [24]. The pores in solid materials are classified as intra-particle, inter-particle, and inter-aggregate based on the pore size. Due to the presence of CQDs, the inset plot presents a large inter-particle porosity. The pore size distributions can be interpreted as a large volume of inter-particle pores (2–5 nm) and a small volume of inter-aggregation pores (16–34 nm). Table 1
                         provides information on the BET surface area, pore volume (Vp), average pore diameter (Dp), and particle size (dBET). The sample has average pores falling within the mesoporous size range. The mesoporous pores offer highly specific surfaces on which monomolecular, polymolecular, and pore filling occur through capillary. The BET surface area and total pore volume of ZnO/O-CQDs were measured at 27.827 m2/g and 0.3003 cm3/g, respectively. The measured mean pore diameter and pore volume (Vm) reported about 43.162 nm and 6.39 cm3(STP)/g, respectively.
